Business Brief -- Genovese Drug Stores Inc.:
   Charge of $615,000 Is Set
   Against 4th-Period Earnings
The suit was filed in June 1990 against eight drug store
chains and 10 pharmaceutical trade associations charging
conspiracy to restrain competition and control prices in
retail pharmacies. Under the settlement, the various
defendants refunded the state $5 million. None of the
defendants admitted or denied any of the charges.